BFN 

  [Text] It has been learned from reliable sources that 
three Palestinian businessmen, together with Bassam Abu-Sharif, 
President Yasir Arafat's adviser, are currently studying a joint 
project for to set up a private television station in the 
autonomy area. 
  Visitors from Amman say that the four held a meeting last 
week at Queen 'Aliya Airport and agreed on the broad outlines of 
their project, including the fact that the project will be 
managed by Abu-Sharif. They also agreed to hold another meeting 
soon in order to put the final touches on the project. 

